# Commit messages

Format: `type(scope): message` or `type: message`. Keep messages short, no extended descriptions.

Scope = affected module(s) (top-level folders under src/), comma-separated if multiple; omit when changes affect whole repo.

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | Changes end-user behavior |
| `fix` | Bug fixes |
| `refactor` | Internal changes, same behavior |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config |
| `docs` | Documentation only |

# Rewriting commits

It's okay to amend the last commit if it was made by you and the amendment increases clarity.
